{"id":14881070,"mediaExerciseId":"ea442c39-de75-4dad-90df-0e6d57af6405","exerciseName":"21","chapterName":"7","chapterTitle":"Interest Rates and Bond Valuation","groupId":612313,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":234,"solutions":[{"id":6009749,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this task, **we should determine the current yield of the bond of the company Workman Software. Then we should find the YTM and effective current yield.**\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The current yield tells us how much the holder of the security will earn if he waits until the maturity date. This is the coupon rates percentage of the current price on the market.\n\n$$\\text{current yield}=\\dfrac{\\text{annual coupon payment}}{\\text{current price of the bond}}$$","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The exercise says that the current bond price is 94.31\\% of its face value. Because the face value is not given, let's assume it is \\$1,000.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{current bond price}&=94.31\\%\\times\\$1,000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\boxed{\\$943.1}\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe current price of the bond is \\$934.1.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/b26e7a1004f72218af786271b052035a/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/b26e7a1004f72218af786271b052035a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, let's calculate the annual coupon payment. Coupon rates are determined by the entity that issues a bond. The coupon value will be the same for every future payment. So it is a fixed amount.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{annual coupon payment}&=\\text{annual coupon rate}\\times\\text{face value}\\\\[15pt]\n&=6.4\\%\\times\\$1,000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$64\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe annual coupon payment is \\$64.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":206,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/dbff474e86fb8f0fbcc01cf9c77fd58d/lateximg_large.png","width":998},"regular":{"height":104,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/dbff474e86fb8f0fbcc01cf9c77fd58d/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**a)**\n\nNow, we have all the data to calculate the current yield.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{current yield}&=\\dfrac{\\$64}{\\$943.1}\\times 100\\\\[15pt]\n&=0.06786\\times100\\\\[15pt]\n&=6.78\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The current yield is 6.78\\%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":285,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/eac25cffe10983ff05c9767777fcf672/lateximg_large.png","width":992},"regular":{"height":143,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/eac25cffe10983ff05c9767777fcf672/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"**b)**\n\nWe can classify yield to maturity as a return rate. More specifically, yield to maturity is what an investor will earn if he holds the bond until the maturity date when the issuer pays back all the promised interest payments and the amount of the debt written in the contract (principal).","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":400,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/7dc866e336f67df39e0642b829f0923f/lateximg_large.png","width":1014},"regular":{"height":201,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/7dc866e336f67df39e0642b829f0923f/lateximg.png","width":507}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"The bond payment will be twice per year(semiannually), but we have an annual coupon rate and YTM. That is why we should divide the YTM and the coupon rate by two. A period is given annually, but we should multiply it by two. The bondholder will not get payments 18 times, but 36 (two times per year). The best way to calculate YTM is to use Spreadsheets.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":395,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/6bf12deaa8d79ef4ce4987357d658ec6/lateximg_large.png","width":744},"regular":{"height":198,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/6bf12deaa8d79ef4ce4987357d658ec6/lateximg.png","width":372}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's adjust the coupon rate.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{semiannual coupon rate}&=\\dfrac{\\text{annual coupon rate}}{2}\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\dfrac{6.4\\%}{2}\\\\[15pt]\n&=3.2\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nThe semiannual coupon rate is 3.2\\%.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":183,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/6fd61adc0c9f3355c0cff8490993f8ee/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":92,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/6fd61adc0c9f3355c0cff8490993f8ee/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"The semiannual coupon payment will be:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{semiannyal coupon payment}&=3.2\\%\\times\\$1,000\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\$32\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":183,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/4798dc8fa721592e7b842cb42e8aa045/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":92,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/4798dc8fa721592e7b842cb42e8aa045/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's adjust the periods.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{semiannual periods}&=\\text{annual periods}\\times2\\\\[15pt]\n&=18\\times2\\\\[15pt]\n&=36\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWe should consider 36 periods in the formula.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":569,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/ee48405c145a3fc8b394ecb434824695/lateximg_large.png","width":803},"regular":{"height":286,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/ee48405c145a3fc8b394ecb434824695/lateximg.png","width":403}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":10},{"columns":[{"text":"Now, we have all the data to calculate the YTM.\n\n$$\\text{Price}=\\text{C}\\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{-n}}{\\text{YTM}}+\\dfrac{\\text{P}}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^\\text{n}}$$\n\nC-coupon of the bond \n\nYTM-yield to maturity\n\nP-par value\n\nn-time","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":323,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/4afd43d05705b89927604093bf289709/lateximg_large.png","width":768},"regular":{"height":163,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/4afd43d05705b89927604093bf289709/lateximg.png","width":383}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":11},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's insert all the data in the previous formula.\n\n$$\\$943.1=\\$32\\times\\dfrac{1-\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^{-36}}{\\text{YTM}}+\\dfrac{\\$1,000}{\\left(1+\\text{YTM}\\right)^{36}}$$\n\n**YTM=6.944%**\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":289,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/04e0cd4bb81abec22077d3ffa583fad1/lateximg_large.png","width":797},"regular":{"height":146,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/04e0cd4bb81abec22077d3ffa583fad1/lateximg.png","width":398}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":12},{"columns":[{"text":"**c)**\n\nNow, we should find an effective annual yield. This tells us what the holder will earn in total from the investments.\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text{effective annual yield}&=\\left(1+\\dfrac{\\text{r}}{\\text{n}}\\right)^\\text{n}-1\\\\[15pt]\n&=\\left(1+\\dfrac{6.78\\%}{18}\\right)^{18}-1\\\\[15pt]\n&=0.07001\\times100\\\\[15pt]\n&=7.001\\%\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\n**The effective annual yield is 7.001\\%.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":189,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/cbf9613cc12c2ac530696cf0b915c3dd/lateximg_large.png","width":832},"regular":{"height":96,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/12/7ce91d2182a043446fd7772b0e36d576/cbf9613cc12c2ac530696cf0b915c3dd/lateximg.png","width":416}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":13}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"d6cfe0b6-e4ab-48a0-8b23-e66405462475","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":13}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":